Short: Base for all types and resources
Definition: Defines the basic properties of every data value. This is an abstract type, meaning that no value can be just a data value without belonging to any concrete type. Every concrete type is a specialization of this general abstract DataValue type.

Label: Exceptional Value Detail
Definition: If a value is an exceptional value (NULL-value), this specifies in what way and why proper information is missing.
When valued in an instance, this attribute signals the imposition of realm-specific constraints. The value of this attribute identifies the realm in question

When valued in an instance, this attribute signals the imposition of constraints defined in an HL7-specified message type. This might be a common type (also known as CMET in the messaging communication environment), or content included within a wrapper. The value of this attribute provides a unique identifier for the type in question.
Condition(s): II-1:An II instance must have either a root or an nullFlavor. {root.exists() or nullFlavor.exists()}

Label: Exceptional Value Detail
Definition: If a value is an exceptional value (NULL-value), this specifies in what way and why proper information is missing.

Label: Assigning Authority Name
Definition: A human readable name or mnemonic for the assigning authority. The Assigning Authority Name has no computational value. The purpose of a Assigning Authority Name is to assist an unaided human interpreter of an II value to interpret the authority. Note: no automated processing must depend on the assigning authority name to be present in any form.

Label: Displayable
Definition: Specifies if the identifier is intended for human display and data entry (displayable = true) as opposed to pure machine interoperation (displayable = false).

Label: Root
Definition: Identifies the type as an HL7 Registered model

Label: Extension
Definition: A character string as a unique identifier within the scope of the identifier root.

Label: Root
Short:
- Pour un professionnel : '1.2.250.1.71.4.2.1'
- Pour le patient/usager : OID de l'autorité d'affectation de l'INS
- Pour un système de structure : '1.2.250.1.71.4.2.1' 
- Pour un SNR : OID de l'éditeur 
- Pour le DP : '1.2.250.1.71.4.2.1'
Definition: A unique identifier that guarantees the global uniqueness of the instance identifier. The root alone may be the entire instance identifier.

Label: Extension
Short:
Valeur de l’identifiant.
- Pour le PS, valeur de PS_IdNat (voir CI-SIS_ANX_SOURCES-DONNEES-PERSONNES-STRUCTURES).
- Pour le patient/usager, valeur de l'INS du patient/usager.
Definition: A character string as a unique identifier within the scope of the identifier root.

Label: Exceptional Value Detail
Definition: If a value is an exceptional value (NULL-value), this specifies in what way and why proper information is missing.

Label: Code
Definition: The plain code symbol defined by the code system. For example, "784.0" is the code symbol of the ICD-9 code "784.0" for headache.

Label: Code System
Definition: Specifies the code system that defines the code.

Label: Code System Name
Definition: The common name of the coding system.

Label: Code System Version
Definition: If applicable, a version descriptor defined specifically for the given code system.

Label: Display Name
Definition: A name or title for the code, under which the sending system shows the code value to its users.
The valueSet extension adds an attribute for elements with a CD dataType which indicates the particular value set constraining the coded concept.
The valueSetVersion extension adds an attribute for elements with a CD dataType which indicates the version of the particular value set constraining the coded concept.

Label: Original Text
Definition: The text or phrase used as the basis for the coding.

Label: Qualifier
Definition: Specifies additional codes that increase the specificity of the the primary code.

Label: Translation
Definition: A set of other concept descriptors that translate this concept descriptor into other code systems.

Short:
Personne physique : 
- Obligatoire pour un professionnel 
- Obligatoire pour un patient/usager 
- Non utilisé pour un SNR 
- Non utilisé pour le DP

Structure de rattachement :
- Pour un PS : Organisation pour le compte de laquelle intervient le PS.
- Pour un patient : seul l'élément standardIndustryClassCode est renseigné (cas particulier des documents d'expression personnelle du patient).
